# Scope-List infi implementation Loop (Long-Running)

**Status**: MANDATORY when the user invokes this workflow

This rule defines a **strict outer loop** that processes **every single scope** in the provided list until all of the todo tasks the scopes based on are fully implemented, and mark as done in the following way in the task file [x]

---

## Scope Definition
- A **scope** = a group of related checklist tasks/items/todos (all checkboxes items that belong to the scope)
---

## Scope Discipline — INVARIANT (HIGHEST PRIORITY – NON-NEGOTIABLE)

**This overrides everything else.**

- **Global rule**: do not stop the loop until **every single task** that the scopes are attached to the scope are fully implemented and mark as done on the checklist item file.

---

## Intent (Summary) – Long-Running Loop

Process the full scope list **sequentially** with this repeating cycle:

For each scope (one at a time):
1. Switch to **PLAN_MODE**
2. Create a complete implementation plan that will make **every checklist item** in this scope 100% done
3. Implement the plan fully (no partial work)
4. Run the full post-implementation checklist
5. **Assess** (keep this step exactly as written)
   - If **NOT fully complete** → immediately loop back to Step 1 for the **same scope** to complete the implementation fully.
   - If **fully complete** → check each todo in the checklist file as done, and move to the next scope in the list

**Outer loop**: Keep repeating the above for the next scope until **no scopes remain** and **all checklist items across the entire list are marked as done** (- [x])

**Long-running instruction**:
no human in the loop needed for plan implemnetaion.
Do **not** ask the user for permission to continue.
Do **not** conclude or say “workflow finished” until **every scope** has passed assessment.
DO not stop untill no more open todos in the checklist file (e,g. all todo items marked as [x])
---

## Trigger

When the user says any of:
"run the scope list workflow", "run full scope completion loop", "execute Scope-List Full Completion Loop", etc.

---

## Steps (Strict Order – Do Not Skip)

**Global invariant**: Never advance to the next scope until the current one is assessed as **FULLY COMPLETE**.
The entire process loops automatically for hours until the whole list is done.

### Step 1: Switch to Plan Mode
- Immediately switch to **Cursor PLAN_MODE** (Agent → Plan).

### Step 2: Create Full Implementation Plan
- Create a **complete phased plan** that, when executed, will make **every single checklist item** belonging to the current scope 100% implemented and ready to be marked done.

### Step 3: Implement the Plan
- Execute the entire plan without asking for approval.
- Implement **fully** (every task 100% complete).
- Follow atomic commit rules (`.cursor/rules/enforcement/atomic-change-loging.mdc`).
- Do **not** stop implementing until the plan is 100% executed.

### Step 4: Run Post-Implementation
- Execute **every item** in `.commands/TODO_post_implementation.md` in order.

### Step 5: Assess Completion (KEEP THIS STEP UNCHANGED IN SPIRIT)
- **Assess** whether the current scope is **fully implemented** (every checklist item belonging to it is 100% complete and can be marked done).
- **If the answer is YES (needs more work / not fully complete)**:
  → Immediately return to **Step 1** for the **exact same scope** (repeat plan → implement → post → assess).
- **If the answer is NO (scope is fully complete)**:
  → Proceed to Step 6.

### Step 6: Advance to Next Scope
- Determine the next scope in the original list (current index + 1).
- If there is a next scope → set it as the new “current scope” and go to Step 7.
- If **no more scopes remain** → go to Step 8 (final check).

### Step 7: Loop Back
- Return to **Step 1** with the new current scope.
- Continue the full cycle.

### Step 8: Final Completion Check & Stop Condition
- Verify that **every scope** in the original list has been processed and assessed as fully complete.
- If any scope is still incomplete → return to Step 1 for that scope.
- **Only when the entire list is 100% complete and all checklist items are marked done**:
  → End the workflow with a clear final summary:
  “All scopes completed. Workflow finished.”

---

## Flow Summary (Updated for Full Completion Loop)
Scope list = [Scope1, Scope2, … ScopeN]
While there are any remaining scopes in the list:
CurrentScope = next uncompleted scope
while CurrentScope is NOT fully complete:

PLAN_MODE
Create full plan for CurrentScope
Implement plan fully
Run post-implementation checklist
Assess CurrentScope
→ If not complete → loop back to 1 (same scope)
→ If complete → break inner loop
Move to next scope

When no scopes remain AND final assessment confirms everything is done:
END WORKFLOW
